input: World Sake Day or "Nihonshu no Hi" is a significant day on the Japanese calendar with celebrations held annually on 1 October. This date is considered "New Year's Day" for sake because it marks the first day of the sake
continuation: season . Sake is an alcoholic beverage made from fermented rice , generally aged for a year or more .Sake is often served in the form of a small glass or bottle . In Japan , sake is usually offered in a " sake cup " or " sake goblet " which is a flat , hollow glass bowl with a small opening at the bottom .Sake cups are often decorated with the image of a sakura flower , a Japanese flower with pink petals . Sake is a popular beverage in Japan , with many people consuming it every day .In indeed , sake eating is so extensive that it is regarded a component of Japanese culture . Sake has a long tradition in Japan .The first sake was produced by Japanese monks in the 4th century BC . During the Edo period ( 1603 - 1868 ) , sake was imported from China and Japan .Today , the most famous sake products in Japan are produced by the Asahi , Kirin , Nisshin , Suntory , and Asahi - Suntory breweries . input: NEW YORK  One recent spring morning in the Utah desert, Jerry Foote received an ecstatic e-mail that gravitational forces were causing two stars to orbit each other, with one star swallowing matter from its companion. Rudolf Novak received the same message
continuation: , but it was from a different source . Foote , a physicist at the University of California , Berkeley , and Novak , an astrophysicist at the University of California , Santa Cruz , were two of the first scientists to identify gravitational waves , the ripples in space - time generated by the merging of two white holes .It was a very exciting day , Foote explained . It was like , Wow , weve learned something .The observation of gravitational waves , which was reported in the journal Nature on Wednesday , has opened up a new frontier in science . Scientists have known for decades that black holes can create ripples in space - time , but the first time they were detected , in 2015 , scientists were not certain what to make of them .Its been a long time come , Novak said . The first time they were detected , we thought , Oh , theyre just noise .Gravitational waves , which are also known as ripples in the fabric of space - time , were first anticipated by Albert Einstein in 1915 . TRUCKEE, Calif.  Property owners this week overwhelmingly approved a special tax to fund maintenance for the Brickelltown streetscape project.
At Tuesdays Truckee Town Council meeting, returned mailed ballots (30 out of 34
continuation: ) showed support for the taxation , which will be levied on property buyers in the Brickelltown area . If passed by voters , the taxation will be charged on the assessed value of property in the area , and will be paying by land owners .The tax will be assessed at $ 4 per $ 100 , 000 of assessed value , and will be levied on property buyers in Brickelltown , the Village of Truckee , and Truckee Meadows Community College . The tax is expected to produce about $ 1 . 5 million per month , which will be used to restore the streetscape project .The streetscape project will include the installation of sidewalks , road lights , landscaping , and other amenities . The project will also strengthen the pedestrian experience in the area , with the installation of a new pedestrian crossing at the intersection of Brickell Avenue and South Truckee Boulevard .The project is expected to be completed by the end of the year . For more information on the Brickelltown streetscape project , view the project page at https : / / www . truckeetown . org / brickelltown - streetscape / .

continuation: town America , where folks are often friendly and the local fire department is a family affair . But in this part of the world , the volunteer fire department is a huge business ." It ' s a family affair , " added Fire Chief Joseph D ' Agostino . " You realize it ' s a family business . "The Hudson County Volunteer Fire Department , which covers a four - square - mile area , has more than 500 members , comprising firefighters , paramedics , dispatchers , administrative staff and volunteers . The department is a non - profit , but it pays for its machinery , notably its cars and engines .It additionally pays for its own maintenance and upgrades , and for fuel . D ' Agostino said the agency ' s spending is about $ 1 million a year ." It ' s a very expensive department , " he said . input: CANBERRA, Australia -- A four-year search of the depths of the Indian Ocean has failed to find Malaysia Airlines Flight 370. But the unprecedented sonar hunt for the missing airliner might be close to solving 19th century mysteries - the locations of
continuation: the wreckage of the world ' s longest - ran shipwreck . The hunt for the aircraft , which vanished on March 8 , 2014 , has been plagued by bad weather and delays , but Australian officials say they are convinced they are close to finding the wreckage ." We are optimistic that we will locate the aircraft , " Australian Transport Minister Darren Chester said . The quest for the Boeing 777 - 200ER was launched in January 2014 after the aircraft ' s last known site was traced to a isolated part of the Indian Ocean .Chester said the sonar search , which has covered an area of 1 , 000 square kilometers ( 380 square miles ) , had unsuccessful to find the aircraft . Polands ruling conservative government has moved to reinstate supreme court judges it forcibly retired, acting on an injunction issued by Europes highest court.
On Wednesday the Law and Justice (PiS) party submitted the relevant legislation on
continuation: the issue to parliament . The European Court of Human Rights ( ECHR ) in Strasbourg had ruling in March that the PiS regime had broken the law by temporarily removing judges from their posts .The ECHR said the courts had been  illegally removed  and had not been given an opportunity to defend themselves . Poland  s supreme court had ordered the reinstatement of the courts , but the authorities said it would go ahead with the move anyway .The ECHR said the Polish government had failed to justify its ruling to remove the courts . The government  s move to reinstate the courts was the latest in a string of moves by the PiS regime that has raised worries in the West about the erosion of judicial sovereignty in Poland .The PiS cabinet , which arrived to power in 2015 , has also introduced a law on judicial change that it said is required to counter corruption . But critics say the law , which would eliminate some legal independence , is part of a broader move by PiS to tighten its grip on the judiciary .The European Commission , the EU  s executive arm , has advised Poland that it could face legal action over the legal improvements .

Security always comes down to securing applications.
The whole point of firewalls is to hide internally deployed network applicationsassumed to have exploitable vulnerabilities somewherefrom the outside world.
The main weakness of firewalls is that they are
continuation: a network security tool , not a network entry control tool . They are meant to shield the network from outside raids , not the other way around .The best method to secure applications is to secure them . This is why network access control ( NAC ) technology is so essential .Network access control software is a setting of rules and policies that govern the movement of clients and information across the network . It ' s a way to reduce malicious users from accessing vulnerable data or endpoints .NAC software is utilized in the following ways : To prohibit access to specific applications on a network .
